title: For Sale:  Rare good condition Saiga ak wood. 7.62x39, .308, .223, 410
postcontent:
I don't see a lot of good wood on saigas any more. Synthetic black seems to be all that's importing these days. 
The wood stocks are sought after as it makes the rifles look a little more classy and classic. Maybe like a dragunov little brother. These wood stocks should fit any saiga rifle, the 410 shotgun and maybe the 20g shotgun. Will not fit the 12 gauge without modification.
But even when I do come across saigas with wood stocks the wood is normally beat to s*** and the finish is in disrepair. 
I came across THIS wood set and my rifle wore it only during one plinking trip. And otherwise just sat in the safe wearing this pretty dress. 
This wood is in nearly new condition. It must have been taken off its original host right after unboxing in trade for a pistol grip configuration. 

This sets grain travel and color also match superbly!  Even when you get good wood on these its not uncommon to see different colors or directions of grain. This set must've come from the same hunk of wood!

I've seen wood in lesser quality than this sell for $100 on the saiga-12 forums and there were no regrets. I'm putting this up for $80obo for a quick sale and hopefully it finds a non-abusive home where its quality is appreciated. 

If you are wondering "why wood stocks" I answer this "the wood creates a MUCH improved balance on these rifles, enhances the cheek weld and lines your eye up perfectly (these were made specific to these guns) and in my opinion every saiga should have wood furniture as it really just looks SOOOO damned good!  

If you're interested please text me at (52O)55l-O555 or for best luck send me an email through this add. Include your contact information if you like.

title: For Sale:   Czech Mauser 8mm VZ24
postcontent: Czech 8mm Mauser, part of the "Romanian Contract" of the 1930s era, in great condition. Non matching numbers, partially scrubed crest, no splits or cracks in the stock, clean looking apart from 80 years of dings, 50% bluing, which is not bad considering its age.The bore is dark & frosty, which is usual, but theres more than plenty of rifling in there. Technical Background          Get Started         Contact Us         Springfield-Armory.com
Springfield Armory® is initiating this voluntary safety recall to upgrade 3.3 XD-S™ 9mm and 3.3 XD-S™ .45ACP pistols with new components, which eliminate the possibility of a potentially dangerous condition. We want to emphasize that no injuries have been reported to date.

Springfield has determined that under exceptionally rare circumstances, some 3.3 XD-S™ 9mm and .45ACP caliber pistols could experience an unintended discharge during the loading process when the slide is released, or could experience a double-fire when the trigger is pulled once. The chance of these conditions existing is exceptionally rare, but if they happen, serious injury or death could occur.

What should you do?
STOP USING YOUR 3.3 XD-S™ 9mm or .45ACP PISTOL AND CAREFULLY UNLOAD IT! 

To begin the upgrade process and for fastest response, click on the Get Started link at the top of the page. On that page enter your serial number and click Next.  If your pistol is subject to this recall, you will need to provide your name, address, phone number, and email address.  The serial number is located on the frame beneath the dust cover (accessory rail).  If you prefer, you may initiate the upgrade process by calling REDACTED.  If you no longer own the 3.3 XD-S™ 9mm or .45ACP pistol, please advise Springfield of the current owner.

XD-S Serial Number

What pistols are involved?
This Safety Recall applies only to:
Springfield 3.3 XD-S™ 9mm pistols - serial numbers between XS900000 and XS938700 
Springfield 3.3 XD-S™ .45ACP pistols - serial numbers between XS500000 and XS686300.

This Safety Recall does not apply to any XD® or XD(M)® pistols.

What will Springfield do?
Springfield will send you a return authorization and mailing label, allowing you to return your 3.3 XD-S™ 9mm or .45ACP pistol to Springfield at no cost to you.  Springfield will upgrade your 3.3 XD-S™ 9mm or .45ACP pistol with the new components, and return it to you.  Springfield will provide tracking numbers so you can monitor the receipt and return of your upgrades.

Questions?
Visit www.springfield-armory.com for further information about this safety recall. You can reach the Springfield Armory Call Center at REDACTED.  Springfield apologizes for this inconvenience, but your safety is our paramount concern.

We greatly appreciate your loyalty to Springfield products.
